    <h2>The Real Problem: Three Root Causes, Not One</h2>

    <p>FastBots' homepage states the chatbot "always has the right answer" <strong>Vendor Claim</strong>. This is aspirational marketing — no RAG-powered chatbot achieves 100% accuracy. When your FastBots chatbot gives wrong answers, the cause traces to one of three independent root causes, each requiring a different fix <strong>Verified</strong>.</p>

    <Callout type="info">
      <strong>Core framework:</strong> Accuracy problems in RAG-powered chatbots stem from three independent root causes — knowledge base rot (stale or outdated content), RAG retrieval gaps (poor document structure preventing correct chunk retrieval), and model variance (different models produce different quality answers). Each requires a different fix. These factors can also compound: a user could have all three problems simultaneously.
    </Callout>

    <p>Accuracy problems in RAG-powered chatbots trace to three independent root causes: knowledge base rot (stale or outdated content preventing correct answers), RAG retrieval gaps (poor document structure preventing the system from finding the right information), and model variance (different AI models producing different quality outputs) <strong>Verified</strong>. Industry sources consistently converge on this three-factor framework: Nerova's diagnostic guide identifies "weak grounding, stale content, vague instructions, or missing escalation rules" as primary causes <strong>Third-Party Reported</strong>, HappySupport confirms that "knowledge base structure determines retrieval quality more than model choice or prompt engineering" <strong>Third-Party Reported</strong>, and NVIDIA's technical research establishes that chunking strategy directly affects retrieval precision by 15-30% <strong>Verified</strong>.</p>

    <p>These three factors can compound each other. A FastBots user could simultaneously have stale training data, poorly structured source documents, and a free-tier model that hallucinates more frequently. The framework below helps you isolate which problem you have — because treating the wrong root cause wastes time and money.</p>

    <Callout type="warn">
